  "local_port": 43708,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I collect movie tickets booked on BookMyShow?",
  "response": "To collect movie tickets booked on **BookMyShow**, follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **E-Ticket (Digital Ticket)**\n   - Most tickets booked on BookMyShow are delivered as **e-tickets** (digital tickets) via email or SMS.\n   - After booking, you\u2019ll receive a confirmation email or SMS with a QR code or booking ID.\n   - **At the theater**, simply show the QR code on your phone at the entrance or ticket counter. They will scan it to verify your booking.\n   - Ensure your phone screen is bright and the QR code is clearly visible.\n\n### 2. **Printing the E-Ticket (Optional)**\n   - If you prefer a physical ticket, you can **print the e-ticket** from the confirmation email or PDF provided by BookMyShow.\n   - Carry the printed ticket to the theater and present it at the entrance or ticket counter.\n\n### 3. **Box Office Collection**\n   - Some theaters may require you to collect physical tickets from the **box office**.\n   - In this case, ensure you carry:\n     - The **booking ID** or **reference number** from your confirmation email/SMS.\n     - A **valid ID proof** matching the name on the booking.\n   - Go to the box office, provide the details, and collect your ticket.\n\n### 4. **BookMyShow App**\n   - Log in to the **BookMyShow app** on your phone.\n   - Go to **My Tickets** or **Bookings** to access your ticket details and QR code.\n   - Show the QR code at the theater for entry.\n\n### 5. **Kiosk Collection**\n   - Some theaters have **self-service kiosks** where you can collect your tickets.\n   - Use the **booking ID** or scan the QR code at the kiosk to print your tickets.\n\n### Tips:\n   - Arrive at the theater **at least 30 minutes before the showtime** to avoid last-minute rushes.\n   - Ensure your phone is charged if you're using an e-ticket.\n   - Keep a backup of your ticket details (screenshot or print) in case of connectivity issues.\n\nIf you face any issues, contact **BookMyShow Customer Support** via their app, website, or helpline.",
